<data dir="mp3/">
	<!-- 
		Soundfiles are listed below in three sections, music for BG music loops and stings, sfx for sound effects and vo for Voice Overs
		
		Each group is a sound channel.  Music will stop any music playing when triggered, voice over does the same.  SFX will allow any number of SFX files to play concurrently.
		
		Each soundfile has a file attribute for the file name (no  file type ending!), optional id, volume 0-100, optional loops and packName
		
		EAch soundfile can have an optional platform attribute of mobile or desktop to play only on those platforms
		
		Asset packs listed should have folders labeled music, sfx and vo and match groupings.
		
		The sound files can be played by file name or id.  If using id, all files with ID will play in listed order when calling SoundPlayerRemote.play().
		Use the SoundplayerRemote.playRandom or .playSequential to play only one file in the group
	-->
